Version 1.16.4                                                      2007-02-23
==============================================================================

1.    NEW FEATURES
      
      CR20006546
      Ant 1.7.0
      
      Ant 1.7.0 support added.
      
2.    CHANGES
     
2.0.  CHANGED FEATURES
      none
      
2.1.  FIXED BUGS

      CR20006545 
      openmdx:manifest
      
      openmdx:manifest should be renamed to openmdx:archivemanifest
      
      The former name leads often to exceptions such as refid not suppurted
      by manifest etc.
      
      SF1502604
      junit jar availability test broken

      The availability test in etc/ant/build-library.xml for the availability 
      of the junit jar is broken because it tests for the existence of a 
      particular file in a particular directory; however, the jar file may be 
      installed elsewhere (e.g. in ${user.home}/.ant/lib/) and under a 
      different name (e.g. junit-4.1.jar).
      
      Also note that assuming you can copy a file into the ant installation
      directly is broken, because that may be allowed if it was installed 
      from an rpm (hence is not writable by non-root users); the 
      ${user.home}/.ant/lib/ location is a safer place for such things.
                  
2.2.  DEPRECATED FEATURES
      none

2.3   REMOVED FEATURES
      none

 
==============================================================================
Version 1.11.4                                                      2005-11-18
==============================================================================

1.    NEW FEATURES

      CR0006026
      Archive task should support duplicate attribute 
      
      The duplicate attribute defines the behaviour when a duplicate file is 
      found.
 
      Valid values are
      * "add" (keep both of the files)
      * "preserve" (keep the first version of the file found)
      * "fail" (throw a build exception)

      The default value is "add". 
      The value is restricted to "add" in case of  case of "tar" archives.
                                     
2.    CHANGES
     
